The paper deals with signal estimation from non-linear observations, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of the generalized Lasso for this problem makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the single-index model of non-linearity, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper provides theoretical accuracy guarantees for compressed sensing, which is a subfield of signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT).
